0) The data/ directory and the db file must be writeable by others.
The directory must be writeable to allow the creation of temporary
files (journal) by the sqlite process.

1) adm_WT3UZXj1H6J5bzlggDw8.php is actually adminer-4.1.0-en.php
Changed its name so that it's harder to call by chance.

2) If PHP has no support for openssl (no library compiled in), one
can use phpsec instead. If it is however available, see signature_example.php

3) pubkey.pem is the RSA certificate used to verify the signature of uploaded
data.

4) Data are kept encoded in UTF-8
